<div style="animation:fadeIn 6s ease-out forwards;">
<div class="page-container">
<div style="background: rgba(54, 69, 79, 0.7);border: 3px double grey;box-shadow: 0 0 1em grey;padding: 15px;margin: 2em; animation:sway 5s infinite ease-in-out; transition:all 0.3s ease;"><span style="font-family: Gloria Hallelujah;">


<center><span style="font-family: The Girl Next Door;">After all this time... I finally made that trip. You are beautiful...</span></center>


A girl, could not be older than 18, knelt in front of the pylon. A pylon, an ordinary pylon. Red, flickering lights at the top, wires connecting it to other ones, what someone would see on the side of the road. Yet, it was so special to her. Something about it could make her do anything to be able to see it. Anything, even walking thousands of miles to see it.

<center><span style="font-family: The Girl Next Door;">Oh, the sweet eyes you have...</span></center>


The admirer started speaking. The tone hinted at an obsession. If this were a cartoon, a red heart would replace her pupils. To speak clearly, she had feelings towards that pylon. Romantic feelings.

<center><span style="font-family: The Girl Next Door;">The odd body you have... it's all so indescribable. Where did I get this overwhelming crush?</span></center>


Let's speak the truth here. She's an ordinary person. What lead her to this fate was looking away at the wrong time. Shall I paint the scene?

<div style="background: rgba(112, 66, 20, 0.5);border: 3px double grey;box-shadow: 0 0 1em grey;padding: 15px;margin: 2em;color: wheat;transform: rotate(-2deg);">

It was never the girl's fault for liking something so lifeless and inhuman. She was not in the right spot. The girl felt like a total waste of oxygen, and wandered mindlessly. All that was wanted was a family. A family that could love her, no matter if it was biological or metaphorical.

Her wish came true while in the [[Level 1|Lurking Lot]]. She met a humble base, barely more than 13 people. There, she met Laurel. Laurel was a woman significantly older than her. Her hair was already gray, her face was wrinkled. She took care of the young Eloise, giving her food, singing to her. To Eloise it felt like she had met the family that was needed. But family is temporary.

They were forced to part when Laurel was mauled by a [[Entity 3|grue]]. Here screams echoed in her mind, the killer's body—or lack thereof—made her bones shiver from the cold. Eloise left the small outpost she had.

Lone and wandering, she traveled through many levels. Survived an earthquake in the [[Level 2|Utility Halls]], survived the many hazards of [[Level 34|the sewers]], and she finally made it to the [[Level 35|next level]]. Here is when she first came upon her twisted lover boy. She didn't even look at it, just saw it in the corner of her eye. They were took under its manipulation, and soon enough it became obsessed. The admirer spent her next few months of living traveling through other levels, trying to spread the "holy pylon".

After the months passed, her controller told her something else to do. Meet it. Walk to it. Its location was unchanged, the girl started going on a journey towards it.</div>

Let's go back to the present. The pylon gave out one final request the girl must make, to prove her love. The message went through.

<center><span style="font-family: DM Serif Display;">Open up the stomach, split it in half.</span></center>


An off request. Something so bizarre that you wouldn't even see it outside of fiction. Even at your lowest, the most odd request would be made without a second thought. A knife was taken from her pocket, and without hesitation she stabbed herself. The pain was unbearable, but it had to be made. If she doesn't, she would fail a simple test. As the admirer was slowly pulling the knife down, they wondered if she even had to do this. Why did they do this? But there's no turning back. With a cut of such length, she fell onto the terrain below. Bleeding out, she realized: She was never loved. It was only using her.

In her last moments of life, all she saw was what looked like tentacles, which grabbed her. Right there, the eyes closed, never to open again.


What cruel monster did this?
</span></div>
