<center><div style="border: 4px double rgba(130,116,127,0.8); padding: 15px; background: rgba(130,116,127,0.65); box-shadow: 0 0 1em rgba(130,116,127,0.8); text-align: center; margin: 3em 3em 1em 3em; margin-top: 2em; font-family: Rangile;"><big><big><big><big>
Description</big></big></big></big></div></center>
<div class="right-image">
[[File:Mechanical Angel.jpg|500px|link=]]
The only documented and confirmed image of the entity.</div>

<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: 'fundead bb';">E</span>ntity 21 ("Mechanized Angels") is a high-voltage lattice transmission pylon with weak structural integrity. The steel framework shows loss of vertical load-bearing integrity, with pronounced deformation on the lattice members, causing buckled asymmetry in the lower areas. Entity 21 has an unmeasurably high Vickers hardness and is immune to all currently known methods of damage. The designation "Mechanized Angels" is both literal and descriptive, with the term "angel" referencing its observed effect on those it affects, rather than any religious or benevolent qualities.

Entity 21's effects manifest only when a subject views it directly, either visually or peripherally. Upon that, the entity will be able to access the subject's mind freely, being able to compel it to perform any actions at its behest, creating a service dependency. The affected individual will still be able to think on its own, although its thoughts will be majorly influenced by the pylon's presence. Most affected people will be unable to get rid of it, resulting in an obsession with Entity 21. Any person who reaches this state is gone and cannot be saved.

The average lifespan of entity 21 relies on its position. It has been observed that instances that reside in drier habitats live longer than those that reside in a habitat with higher humidity. The range of life is roughly 30 to roughly more than 100 years. Once the entity dies, it will no longer have an indamagable surface, with its Vickers vastly lower. This is how most information about the biology of entity 21 comes from.

<div style="align:center;border:#ffffff 2px solid;background:rgba (112,128,144,0.5); margin:auto; padding:1rem; width:80%">
<center><big><big><big><div class="titleblock">How To Save Someone Who Is Under The Effects of Entity 21<span style="font-family: 'Rangile';">?</span></div></big></big></big></center>
If you live in a settlement that is on an outdoor level, it is possible someone in your community may encounter entity 21. In a case of such ever happening, it is important to know what to do, and how to save them from an impending death. A list of tips has been made on what to do if something like such ever happens. If a week passed, and they are still under the effect, they are gone and there's no use in trying to save them.
<center>'''''Notice:'''These tips are unlikely to be effective when attempted on oneself. Do not rely on them for self-recovery!</center>
<center>
----
*The first thing to do is to know whether they are under the effects. The effects come with erratic behavior, spreading throughout Entity 21 and instability. If all three signs are observed—or at least the second—you should follow through. If not, then do not attempt to. The method is inhumane and may cause psychological torture of an unaffected person.
----
*Once it is confirmed, try to lure them into a small, windowless room. Any light that could come from the door should be blocked off, either by shutting the lights off in the room beyond or barricading the door. They must stay there for a week. Be sure to give them food and water every other day without letting them escape. If a room cannot be used, use an old well or any pit that was dug out; they must be in an enclosed space where light cannot access.
----
*After the end of the week, release them. If they continue the erratic behavior, repeat the process, until they stop.
----
<div style="text-align: right;"><small><small>Taken from the oldest recorded survival guide (1571)</small></small></div></center></div>
<center><div style="border: 4px double rgba(130,116,127,0.8); padding: 15px; background: rgba(130,116,127,0.65); box-shadow: 0 0 1em rgba(130,116,127,0.8); text-align: center; margin: 3em 3em 1em 3em; margin-top: 2em; font-family: Rangile;"><big><big><big><big>
Effects</big></big></big></big></div></center>
<div class="left-image">
[[File:Mechanized Angel 2.jpg]]
Photograph of a possibly affected individual. Taken on [[Level 350]].</div>
<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: 'fundead bb';">E</span>ntity 21 has a wide range of effects on the affected individual, which intensify with lack of treatment. The entity is capable of issuing demands and messages via telepathic methods, often compelling them to spread dogma about its presence and presumably about how it saved them. Individuals may say it's voluntary, often having impulsive outbursts. When confronted, they will mention that the entity is watching over them, protecting them from above. All of these are merely delusions of manipulation.

Affected individuals may start feeling romantic feelings towards said entity, starting to talk about it affectionately and intimately. They will never anthropomorphize the entity, for some reason, always abiding to the pylon. This attachment can rapidly escalate into an obsession, often accompanied by self-destruction and harmful behavior towards others to prove "devotion". Acts towards others may include murder, torture, abuse, paralyzing others and various other harmful actions.

Subjects affected by Entity 21 may start drawing pylon shapes on any material, using whatever can be accessed. The shape is repetitive, varying slightly. Subjects would feel an urge to draw them, even if they know it is meaningless. Certain rooms have been found filled fully with such drawings. The most ever recorded was 274, all of them packed closely to each other.

<center><div style="border: 4px double rgba(130,116,127,0.8); padding: 15px; background: rgba(130,116,127,0.65); box-shadow: 0 0 1em rgba(130,116,127,0.8); text-align: center; margin: 3em 3em 1em 3em; margin-top: 2em; font-family: Rangile;"><big><big><big><big>
Biology</big></big></big></big></div></center>
<div class="right-image">
[[File:Mechanized dumbfuck.jpg]]
Another image of entity 21, taken on [[level 344]].</div>
<span style="font-size: 20px; font-family: 'fundead bb';">T</span>he biology of Entity 21 remains disputed. The theory most agreed upon is that it has 3 major body regions: the base, the eye, and the tendrils. The body is made out of a thick shell, its texture being reminiscent of leather, steel and somewhat skin to the touch. This outer shell covers the whole body except the eyes.

The base is the largest body region, almost the whole body. As previously noted, it takes the form of an unstable and broken pylon. The inside is made out of a fleshy material, examined through deceased instances of entity 21. The meat of entity 21 isn't edible. It has a sickly red color, although it is possible that it is colored differently due to the tissue coming from already-deceased instances. It has a dry buildup, lacking any substance. It has considerably more carbs than protein and fat.

The tendrils are wire-shaped parts of the body, often connected to other non-entity pylons nearby. The tendrils are thin, have a black color and do not contain any tissue inside. At the connecting point of the tendrils and the base is a small sensor that allows the entity to move it; that sensor is often times regarded as the end of the entity's body, since the rest are perceived as removable extensions. They are not bound to the hardness that the entity contains and can be easily torn off.

The eyes are the smallest part of the body, being a rough cylinder with two connectors to the body. Entity 21 does not necessarily have eyelids, rather just a pile of skin that can come out of the connectors to close the eyes. Entity 21 doesn't need to blink due to being specially evolved to not be sensitive to dust, wind, rain and other natural elements. The middle of the eye has a pupil that is vertically slit for better focus on potential prey.

<center><div style="border: 4px double rgba(130,116,127,0.8); padding: 15px; background: rgba(130,116,127,0.65); box-shadow: 0 0 1em rgba(130,116,127,0.8); text-align: center; margin: 3em 3em 1em 3em; margin-top: 2em; font-family: Rangile;"><big><big><big><big>
Theories</big></big></big></big></div></center>

<div class="titleblock"><span class="titleblock">Theory 1</span><br><center>'''''Hivemind theory'''''</center><br><br>The Hivemind theory suggests the entity is a "hivemind," a single consciousness that is owned by multiple lifeforms (in this case entity 21). This would explain why they emit identical behavior under the control of affected individuals and why many actions done by influenced subjects remain so similar. While this theory seems perfect, it does not have any evidence for its factuality, and is derived from a post on Backchat. Most researchers do not think of it as a fact. The original post on Backchat comes from an anonymous user claiming to have solved the life-cycle of entity 21. When asked for elaboration, they laid out the theory. They said it took some elements from an aged text, the one where Theory 2 comes from.

If it comes out to not be false, it could potentially reshape our current understanding of entity 21, explaining some of the recursive elements. While the theory is based on those recursive elements, it is also it's biggest fallacy; while not all portrayed behavior is the same, only similar. If it were to be the same all throughout, the theory would be more plausible.
</div>

<div class="titleblock"><span class="titleblock">Theory 2</span><br><center>'''''Evil spirit theory'''''</center><br><br>This theory comes from the 17th century. At the time, saying that the entity was controlled by a 'spirit' that moved from pylon to pylon. Every time it moved, the original pylon would die. Affected people were only controlled by the 'spirit,' with it being evil coming from what affected subjects do. This theory is very outlandish nowadays. While the idea of a spirit controlling people could be possible, the entity is an uncontrolled being.</div>
<center><div style="border: 4px double rgba(130,116,127,0.8); padding: 15px; background: rgba(130,116,127,0.65); box-shadow: 0 0 1em rgba(130,116,127,0.8); text-align: center; margin: 3em 3em 1em 3em; margin-top: 2em; font-family: Rangile;"><big><big><big><big>
Do and Don't</big></big></big></big></div></center>
===<center>Do</center>===
*If anyone conveys any signs of being affected, try to save them.
*Do not forget that the commands made do not have to be done. This requires a strong willpower, although it is the only method towards self-recovery.
===<center>Don't</center>===
*Attempt self-recovery using the guide.
*Try to find it.
